revision.text: Possibly: University Education: or, an explication and amendment of the statute which, Under a Penalty insufficient and eluded, prohibits the admission of scholars going from one society to another without the leave of their respective Governors, or of their Chancellor, humbly propos'd To the Chancellor, Masters, and Scholars of the University of Oxford, as a Means necessary to the good education of youth in the said university; on occasion of the late irregular admission of William Seaman, Commoner of Hart-Hall, into Oriel College. By R. Newton, D.D. Principal of Hart-Hall. (London : Printed for G. Strahan, at the Golden-Ball over against the Royal-Exchange, 1726.) http://library.st-andrews.ac.uk/record=b2447809~S1
